[+++ b/docs/reference/cluster/nodes-info.asciidoc, +* `isolation`: whether the plugin is loaded in isolation (`true`) or not (`false`), +++ b/docs/reference/cluster/nodes-info.asciidoc, +* `isolation`: whether the plugin is loaded in isolation (`true`) or not (`false`), +++ b/docs/reference/modules/plugins.asciidoc, +added[1.1.0], +[float], +==== Plugins isolation, +, +Since Elasticsearch 1.1, by default, each plugin is loaded in _isolation_ (in its dedicated `ClassLoader`) to avoid class clashes between the various plugins and their associated libraries. The default can be changed through the `plugins.isolation` property in `elasticsearch.yml`, by setting it to `false`:, +, +[source,js], +--------------------------------------------------, +plugins.isolation: false, +--------------------------------------------------, +, +Do note that each plugin can specify its _mandatory_ isolation through the `isolation` property in its `es-plugin.properties` configuration. In this (rare) case, the plugin setting is used, overwriting whatever default used by Elasticsearch., +, +]